    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-07T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="1053"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1053">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Winterle/14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-07T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 7, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 7—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Embassy’s October 3, 11 a.m.<note n="91" xml:id="d1053fn91">Not
                        printed.</note> and previous. In view of the statement made by Paxton in his
                    October 1, 8 p.m., repeated in my October 2, 3 p.m., that he is satisfied that
                    Navy was involved, I am instructing Paxton to return to Chefoo. He will propose
                    to the Japanese Consul in view of the conflicting reports telegraphed regarding
                    the origin of the affray and the difficulty of arriving at the facts that unless
                    he after consideration has further suggestions for means of arriving at the
                    facts or unless he desires to await outcome Winterle case, either, (1) the case
                    be dropped with mutual oral assurances to make efforts to prevent disturbances
                    involving their respective nationals or, (2), mutual regrets be orally expressed
                    for any participation by police officers and naval personnel that may have
                    occurred with mutual assurances investigation under (1).</p>
                <p>I am instructing Ballantine to remain here pending outcome of this proposal but
                    consider it advisable that he visit Chefoo later irrespective of whether
                    proposal is accepted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
